<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Imitate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Imitate,</orth> 1) to endeavour to resemble, to copy: <bibl n="shak. luc 1137" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1137" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1137</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 67.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 67, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.265" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 265</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.418" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 418</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.221" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 221</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.46" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.201" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 201</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 39</bibl>.<lb />2) to make in imitation, to copy: <cit><quote>the counterfeit is poorly --d after you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 53.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 53, 6</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>